definition: to do/to make/to go in for/to set up/to get hold of/to take care of

sentences.english: Are there any travel behaviors you don’t understand?
sentences.chinese: 你也有許多搞不懂的旅遊習慣嗎？

sentences.english: I wonder why you think this way.
sentences.chinese: 搞不懂你爲什麼恁地想。

sentences.english: I just don't understand the appeal of sitting on the beach all day long.
sentences.chinese: 我就是搞不懂在沙灘上坐一天有什麼吸引人的。

sentences.english: I just can't figure Payton out.
sentences.chinese: 我簡直搞不懂佩頓這個人。

sentences.english: Intellectuals do not understand the genius of the market.
sentences.chinese: 知識分子搞不懂市場的規律。

sentences.english: I couldn't imagine what she meant. The child looked nothing like me.
sentences.chinese: 我真搞不懂她想說啥，孩子一點兒也不像我。

sentences.english: I really couldn't care less about what China does with their internet.
sentences.chinese: 我搞不懂我們爲什麼要管中國的閒事。

sentences.english: We don’t understand the problem why this is the best choice.
sentences.chinese: 我搞不懂這個問題，爲什麼這是最好的選擇。

sentences.english: I don’t get it. Are you asking permission?
sentences.chinese: 我就搞不懂了，你是在請求我許可還是怎樣？

sentences.english: I don't know why he gave me money without rhyme or reason.
sentences.chinese: 我搞不懂他爲什麼平白無故給我錢。

sentences.english: Besides, I can't understand why some medicine can'tbe taken orally, but only intravenously.
sentences.chinese: 而且有的藥沒有口服的，只能輸液，真有些搞不懂。

sentences.english: I don't know how Maradona wants to play.
sentences.chinese: 我也搞不懂，馬拉多納這樣做有什麼道理。

definition: unable to understand/unable to get over
to be unable to guess or make out
to be unable to make any sense of the matter/to be at a loss
see 百思不解[bai3 si1 bu4 jie3]
pinyin: bai3 si1 bu4 de2 qi2 jie3

definition: unable to make sense of what one is looking at
to not understand/to be puzzled by/indissoluble
to remain silent/to have nothing to say/(coll.) speechless/dumbfounded
to blow one's top/to be driven mad/to become frantic
